== I'd Like to Offer My Help ==
I am a native Kapangpangan speaker. I noticed you needed help with audio portions or this book. I can help with that. Let me know. :Thanks, but you haven't left a signature to identify yourself, MetungKP, it makes it easier for us to know who is talking if you sign your message using four tildes like this: <nowiki>~~~~</nowiki>. :--[[User:Lgriot|Lgriot]] ([[User talk:Lgriot|discuss]] • [[Special:Contributions/Lgriot|contribs]]) 11:28, 22 December 2011 (UTC)

{{WikiProject Languages}}

== tsa?? ==

I don't remember us pronouncing tea as literally "tsssa"...  I remember we pronounce it as the Japanese, Korean, and Chinese do, "cha", in fact, we pronounce everything with "ts" as "ch".  The pronunciations need to be checked.--[[Special:Contributions/50.168.47.113|50.168.47.113]] ([[User talk:50.168.47.113|discuss]]) 02:30, 29 September 2013 (UTC)

{{WikiProject Languages}}
For an example of (ㅌ ㄴ) what about 맡는? 맡다 means "keep,carry".[[Special:Contributions/119.202.86.57|119.202.86.57]] ([[User talk:119.202.86.57|discuss]]) 11:42, 22 May 2011 (UTC)

An example for (ㅍ ㅁ) is 앞문 which means "front door".

