Let's start with a definition. [http://www.sourceafis.org/blog/ SourceAFIS] is an [[w:Open-source software|open-source]] [[w:Automated fingerprint identification|Automated Fingerprint Identification System (AFIS)]] that performs [[w:Fingerprint recognition|fingerprint recognition]] (a subfield of [[w:Biometrics|biometrics]]) on pairs or whole databases of human [[w:Fingerprint|fingerprints]].

This book will guide you through first steps with SourceAFIS, advice you on advanced topics, and provide you, if you are curious, with an overview of how SourceAFIS algorithms work.

